column4:
Lynda and I join millions across America in praying for 
@POTUS and @FLOTUS, and all of those impacted by the coronavirus.

I hope my fellow Oklahomans join me in continuing to follow @CDCgov guidelines of washing your hands, wearing a mask, and practicing social distancing.

Just like our communities small businesses, rural hospitals are also feeling the economic pressure of COVID-19.

@RepJasonSmith's Saving Rural Hospitals from Closure Act would help keep our rural hospitals open and ensure no one loses access to healthcare.
https://t.co/bsRnmvG2h3

On Tuesday, @OKcommerce launched Phase 2 of the Oklahoma Business Relief Program.

@OKcommerce and the OBRP are working hard to help local businesses across the state overcome the economic challenges of COVID-19. 

Learn more ↓ https://t.co/pTRv9egeSN

Oklahoma's small businesses are facing tremendous economic disruption due to the #COVID19 outbreak. Need to know which #coronavirus relief option is best for your small business? 

@SBAgov is here to help!
https://t.co/5BfB9wVY5H

Community health centers provide critical care to those who call rural Oklahoma home, and during the #COVID19 outbreak they have a vital role to play. 

@HHSGov has awarded $228,272 to 4 community health centers located in Western Oklahoma. Learn more ↓
https://t.co/d3wCRXo0rb

ICYMI: @LangstonU has partnered with @NASA to develop a natural countermeasure to keep astronauts healthy while in space flight conditions.

@LangstonU continues to be a leader, in Oklahoma and on the world stage, in scientific research &amp; development! 
https://t.co/LVI2IOfSux
